---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { APPS, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = APPS[0]
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Support"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="Support, privacy requests, account deletion, backups, and subscription help for Wardrobe Studio."
>
  <h2>Contact Support</h2>
  <p>
    For help with Wardrobe Studio, contact <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>.
    Estimated response time is 2-5 business days.
  </p>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital
    Product Studio brand.
  </p>
  <p>Suggested subject: Wardrobe Studio Support Request</p>

  <h2>Common Support Topics</h2>
  <p>
    Please include your device model, iOS version, Wardrobe Studio app version if available, and a short
    description of what happened. Do not email passwords or full payment card details.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Account sign-in, email verification, password reset, or account deletion.</li>
    <li>Wardrobe Studio data, backups, imports, photos, widgets, or share extension issues.</li>
    <li>Camera, photo library, location, or notification permission problems.</li>
    <li>Pro entitlement, purchase restore, subscription, or App Store billing questions.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    If you signed in with Apple and used a private relay email address, please contact support from
    that relay address or include enough information to identify your account.
  </p>

  <h2>Subscriptions and Purchases</h2>
  <p>
    All purchases and subscriptions are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store. Subscription
    management, cancellations, and refund requests are handled through the user&apos;s Apple ID account
    and Apple&apos;s App Store settings.
  </p>
  <p>
    To manage or cancel an Apple-billed subscription, open iOS Settings → Apple Account →
    Subscriptions. Refund requests for Apple-billed purchases are handled by Apple through <a
      href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com/"
      >reportaproblem.apple.com</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Privacy and Account Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions, data access requests, correction requests, deletion requests, or account
    deletion support, email <a href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a>. If you use an
    account in Wardrobe Studio, include the email address associated with the account so we can identify
    the request.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you created an account, use the in-app account deletion option where available or contact
    support for assistance. Deleting the app may remove local app data from your device, but it may
    not automatically delete any account or provider-side records.
  </p>

  <h2>Backups and Local Data</h2>
  <p>
    Wardrobe Studio can export a manual JSON backup that may include your clothing photos and wardrobe
    details. Store backup files carefully and delete old copies when you no longer need them.
  </p>
  <p>
    Exported backup files may include wardrobe data, notes, outfit information, wishlist entries,
    and photos if included in the export. Anyone with access to an exported backup file may be able
    to view the information contained in it. Keep exported backups in a safe location and avoid
    sharing them with people you do not trust.
  </p>

  <h2>Legal Documents</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}apps/${app.slug}/privacy-policy/`}>Privacy Policy</a></li>
    <li><a href={`${base}apps/${app.slug}/terms-of-use/`}>Terms of Use</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Legal Note</h2>
  <p>
    These documents are provided for transparency and app publication workflows. They are not a
    substitute for legal advice from a qualified professional.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
